Katsina State government has approved the release of N4.812 billion for the payment of new minimum wage to workers in the state, with effect from January. The state Commissioner for Budget and Planning, Faruq Jobe who stated this while addressing pressmen after the state’s executive council meeting yesterday, said, “ The council has approved the implementation of N30,000 minimum wage to all government workers in the state”. Jobe, however appealed to the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) in the state to also keep to the agreement reached with government by ensuring regular payment of tax in order to improve the internally generated revenue of the state.